  "chapter": {
    "number": 27,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Affirms His Integrity"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Job continued his discourse:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“As surely as God lives, who has deprived me of justice—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Almighty, who has embittered my soul—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "as long as my breath is still within me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the breath of God remains in my nostrils,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "my lips will not speak wickedness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my tongue will not utter deceit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will never say that you are right;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will maintain my integrity until I die.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will cling to my righteousness and never let go.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "As long as I live, my conscience will not accuse me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Wicked Man’s Portion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May my enemy be like the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my opponent like the unjust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For what is the hope of the godless when he is cut off,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when God takes away his life?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will God hear his cry",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when distress comes upon him?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will he delight in the Almighty?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will he call upon God at all times?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will instruct you in the power of God.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not conceal the ways of the Almighty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely all of you have seen it for yourselves.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why then do you keep up this empty talk?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the wicked man’s portion from God—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the heritage the ruthless receive from the Almighty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though his sons are many, they are destined for the sword;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his offspring will never have enough food.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His survivors will be buried by the plague,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their widows will not weep for them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though he heaps up silver like dust",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and piles up a wardrobe like clay,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "what he lays up, the righteous will wear,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his silver will be divided by the innocent.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The house he built is like a moth’s cocoon,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a hut set up by a watchman.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He lies down wealthy, but will do so no more;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when he opens his eyes, all is gone.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Terrors overtake him like a flood;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a tempest sweeps him away in the night.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The east wind carries him away, and he is gone;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it sweeps him out of his place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It hurls itself against him without mercy",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as he flees headlong from its power.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It claps its hands at him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and hisses him out of his place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
